<h3>Details</h3>

The "TaggedPlainCorpus" file type is a text file of category "corpus",
encoded in UTF-8.  Each line represents a sentence. Each sentence
is composed of a sequence of words, separated by a single whitespace.

Each word that could be part of an MWE is represented as

<pre>
    <tt>&lt;mwepart id="LIST_OF_IDS"&gt;</tt>word<tt>&lt;/mwepart&gt;</tt>.
</pre>

Where <tt>LIST_OF_IDS</tt> is a comma-separated list of MWE candidate ID
numbers.


<h3>Escape table</h3>

<p>Substrings involving special characters must be escaped as determined by this table:</p>

<p/>
<table border="1">
 <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Unescaped</th>
      <th>Escaped</th>
      <th>Reason for escaping</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>

    <tr>
      <td>"$"</td>
      <td>"${dollar}"</td>
      <td>This is the escaping character itself.</td>
    </tr>

    <tr>
      <td>"&lt;"</td>
      <td>"${lt}"</td>
      <td>Used by TaggedPlainCorpus to begin a tag.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>"&gt;"</td>
      <td>"${gt}"</td>
      <td>Used by TaggedPlainCorpus to end a tag.</td>
    </tr>

    <tr>
      <td>"\n"</td>
      <td>"${newline}"</td>
      <td>Used by TaggedPlainCorpus to separate sentences.</td>
    </tr>

    <tr>
      <td>" "</td>
      <td>"${space}"</td>
      <td>Used by TaggedPlainCorpus to separate words.</td>
    </tr>

    <tr>
      <td>"#"</td>
      <td>"${hash}"</td>
      <td>Used by the toolkit as a comment prefix.</td>
    </tr>

   </tbody>
  </thead>
</table>

<p>Any output generated by the <code>mwetoolkit</code> will have these characters escaped as well.</p>



<h3>Code comments</h3>

<p>You can add a comment by prefixing any line with the special character "#".</p>




